# Clinical Research Skills Catalog

This project ships a library of task-specific **skills** under the
`skills/<name>/SKILL.md` layout. Each skill is a self-contained playbook
with input spec, method selection, procedure, template code, and output spec.

When a user request matches one of the tasks below, **read the matching
`skills/<name>/SKILL.md` file first** and follow its procedure before
writing any analysis plan or code. Do not reinvent a method that a skill
already specifies.

## How to invoke in Cursor

- Reference the skill directly in chat: `@skills/stat-rct/SKILL.md`
- Or paste the skill's section into Composer context when drafting code
- Multiple skills can be combined for complex tasks (e.g. `stat-cohort`
  + `stat-propensity` for a confounded observational study)

## Skill Index

### Research Planning
| Skill | Use when the user… |
|-------|---------------------|
| `skills/pico-extract/SKILL.md` | …describes a research question needing PICO/PICOS breakdown |
| `skills/pubmed-search/SKILL.md` | …asks for a literature search or prior evidence |
| `skills/study-design/SKILL.md` | …asks which study design fits their question |
| `skills/sample-size/SKILL.md` | …needs a sample size or power calculation |
| `skills/protocol-review/SKILL.md` | …has a study protocol to review (SPIRIT / regulatory) |

### Study-Design-Based Analysis
| Skill | Use when the user… |
|-------|---------------------|
| `skills/stat-rct/SKILL.md` | …runs an RCT (ITT, ANCOVA, MMRM, multiplicity) |
| `skills/stat-cohort/SKILL.md` | …has cohort data (RR, IRR, HR, propensity score) |
| `skills/stat-case-control/SKILL.md` | …has case-control data (OR, conditional logistic) |
| `skills/stat-diagnostic/SKILL.md` | …evaluates a diagnostic test (Se/Sp, ROC/AUC, DCA) |
| `skills/stat-survival/SKILL.md` | …has time-to-event data (KM, Cox, RMST, competing risks) |

